        <h2><i>Words to Song</i> Process</h2>
        <h3>The Proposal</h3>
        <p>
           I had initially used WordPress for my portfolio before I decided to become more proficient in web development. 
           While it fulfilled my needs to an extent, I felt building a portfolio site from scratch to incorporate my development abilities would make more sense. 
        </p>
        <h3>The Process</h3>
        <p>
            I basically took the general layout of the WordPress template that I had used and made it cleaner. 
            Built using the Express framework for Node.js, I decided keeping the most of the content to a single page would be the way to go (unlike the WordPress template).
        </p>
        <p>
            To keep from having to send users to a new page to view the portfolio items, I decided to incorporate a JavaScript menu to toggle the content depending on the category (development, design, or illustrations). 
            Furthermore, I used Lightbox to display the images. 
        <p>
            Rounding out my JavaScript usage, I added a back to top button and incorporated smooth scrolling to target with JQuery. 
        </p>
        <h3>The Progress</h3>
        <p>
            This site is fully functioning the way I had intended. 
            I decided the original color scheme wasn't working for me, so I made some updates to use a palette that felt more "me."
            Outside of the addition of new examples of work, as well as some flashier interactivities in the future, Iâ€™m satisfied with how it turned out. 
        </p>
